The paper deals with image super-resolution using deep learning techniques, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of sparse coding, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves training a neural network, which falls under the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed model on a wide range of images, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
